> This should verify that the selected change output is in the wallet. Bumpfee is intentionally constructed so you can't accidentally rip off the payee using it.

@gmaxwell there is no such check when specifying change address with `fundrawtransaction`, so why do it here?

@luke-jr I think this API is preferable for those that use `fundrawtransaction` with custom change address. I don't consider this and #12096 exclusive, but happily close if #12096 is preferable.

@kallewoof like @luke-jr said above, if there is no change output and an input must be added then a change output could be also added - which would use the specified change.
